        "timestamp": "2021-05-20 09:35:40.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nMay need some assistance from Jessica here to achieve what we are trying.\nUltimately, to stop the older branches from building and pushing the \"latest\" image tag to nexus.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "5eafee0135cae9b46e01e3cd5d4bb2a6ccc2d0c2",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3949,
          "name": "Lasse Kaihlavirta",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "l.kaihlavirt@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "kaihlavi"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-05-20 10:16:29.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n> Patch Set 5:\n> \n> May need some assistance from Jessica here to achieve what we are trying.\n> Ultimately, to stop the older branches from building and pushing the \"latest\" image tag to nexus.\n\nI've noticed that at least oom-platform-cert-service and vnfsdk somehow manage this (the former pushes \"guilin-latest\" instead of \"latest\" from Guilin branch and latter somehow avoid pushing any kind of \"latest\" from Frankfurt branch... which is the newest maintenance release branch it has, but that's a different discussion)\nI didn't look into any details of any of these pushing mechanisms so I have no immediate clues for achieving this in practice, but maybe something for you to look into",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
