        "timestamp": "2021-05-20 18:56:18.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nI think with this change you might still get both master and honolulu pushing \"latest\". \n\nOne way you can control this better, if any of the merge jobs is currently running on a schedule, you might want to set cron: \"\" to disable the schedule. \n\nOtherwise, I think you might be able to modify the docker files or pom.xml files (depending on how the project configures their tagging) to disable the \"latest\" tag for one of the branches. I think this is done in the docker files, right?",
        "patchset_number": 7
