        "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\n> Patch Set 8:\n> \n> > Patch Set 8:\n> > \n> > > Patch Set 8:\n> > > \n> > > Jess - I do not see new gerrit-docker-merge-maintainance job being added - any clue on why?\n> > > \n> > > Only see dcaegen2-services-pmsh-docker-merge-master (https://jenkins.onap.org/view/dcaegen2-services-pmsh/) which is same as before and running on master\n> > \n> > You don't have a docker job under the ID \"gerrit-docker-merge-maintainance\" .. are you adding one?\n> > I think you wanted to use gerrit-docker-merge? with the honolulu stream is it? If you are planning to use the docker merge job from global-jjb, the ID should be gerrit-docker-merge\n> > \n> > If so, please make sure to verify this in the sandbox.\n> \n> Oh okay, got it.\n> Possibly this change outcome was not intended.. currently there is no merge job on honolulu branch.\n> Fiachra - Should this change be reverted?\n\nThe goal was to avoid the \"latest\" tag being overwritten by older branches. My knowledge of how to achieve that is limited. If there are specific JJB templates needed for python projects I don't think it is up to us to define them.",
